 druids, and shaman)<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Pallys can Haste themselves with Luclin, and can cast a choloro-type spell on themselves too. They also have all the cleric spells concerning undead.<br><br>9) Yes, they do rock in duels. High AC/HP, stun, root, bow, and LH makes us one tough opponent.<br><br>So, yah, personnally, I think we'd be a well-respected class if it wasn't for all the losers that chose pallies as their class, hit autoattack, and go AFK.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ufreem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Freem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(2/25/02 7:52:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do pallys get so much crap?</span><hr size=1> Because in a perfect situation paladins would be of little use, at least at the high end game.  Sure we can lay on hands in a situation where a cleric misses a complete heal or to keep a second MT up on an aggro transfer but other then the use of lay on hands we have no unique abilities.  Most folks aren't aware of the class level alt advancement skills that some of us have or are working on.  Instead, to most we are 30 percent cleric and 40 percent warrior or something like that.  I'm not saying we are, I'm saying thats the perception.  There is some truth to it.<br><br>For the average high end encounter (pre Luclin) the most efficient situation would require just enough warriors to keep the defensive disc up, one of each of the classes that can buff them (one ranger for CoP; one shaman to focus/stamina, debuff and slow; one magician for mana rods and to debuff, one or two bards mostly for manasong and debuffing; one enchanter for C2 or Kei and haste; and one paladin for Brell's (group divine strength); a couple monks to get the mob to camp safely; and the rest clerics, rogues and wizards).  Hybrids, other then for their unique buffs, are not as efficient in a raid context as other classes.  One nice thing they do provide however is the ability to fill in where needed.  If your short healing then toss on wisdom/mana gear and play a healing paladin.  If your short damage dealers but heavy on healing then get in there and melee.<br><br>I think in large measure the reason we get so much crap is because most remember when we did little damage.  With the move to the old warrior damage table and the modification of many high end weapons we do incredible damage now, particularly to undead with the Slay Undead 3 skill.  Our reputation for doing little damage is our legacy however albiet an inaccurage one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucereborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cereborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#333333>(2/25/02 10:00:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.machina-ex.com/temp/cereborn140.jpg HEIGHT=160 WIDTH=140></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do pallys get so much crap?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;2) Paladins are one of the two classes that can rez (at high levels).&quot;</b><!--EZCODE B