lign=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do pallys get so much crap?</span><hr size=1> Necros can do a lot more then res and feign death.  My point wasn't that the classes listed weren't useful.  Some encounters it would help to have dmf on, necros can add buffs and heals during combat too at high levels with new Luclin spells.  My point was that no matter what Verant does to add tidbits to the rest of the classes to keep at least one of them useful on a raid the game isn't going to happen without the battery of pitcher and catcher (warrior and cleric).  The rest of us are there either to do damage (wizard and rogue), bring the mob to camp without a ton of adds and do some damage (monk), or buff and do a little more damage (everyone else).  Certain classes will have more of a role then they do in some encounters but generally thats the way its percieved.<br><br>Hawaii asked why we get so much crap.  One reason is because we play the utility player who steps up to make a big play on occassion but otherwise is usually found in the outfield. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bthecrossroadstavern8833.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vallos>Vallos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/02 10:19:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do pallys get so much crap?</span><hr size=1> Necro rezz gives 95 % or so xp back.Paladins do good damage but its slightly less than rangers as well with lower hp and ac then an equally equiped warrior of the same lvl.The paladin is still a powerfull class though, and most of the problem seems to come from other paladins spreading how much they hate there class for whatever reaso