us only on damage output.  The healing ability of a paladin is far too underestimated in my opinion.<br><br>There are many things a paladin does on a high end raid other then cast divine strength or Brell's.  Try keeping a warrior alive when his defensive has run out and he has complete aggro on a mob quading for 1000s and complete heals take 10 seconds to cast.  Try keeping your group alive when clerics are focusing on the main tank thats tanking the boss your after and people are getting heal aggro, rampage aggro or taking damage tanking adds.  Try the 5270 crits on undead with Slay Undead 3.  Try being the primary caster of Cure Greater Curse for a raid of 60 plus people when half are getting hit with a curse that will kill them or rob all their mana in a few seconds.  I could go on and on.<br><br>I wouldn't want to play another class.  What fun would it be to play another class without so much to do?  Warrior, get aggro and hit taunt, swap in a few weapons depending upon the encounter and hit defensive if the mob does too much damage while staying in range of your heals.  Cleric, time your heals to keep your tank alive and be as economical on mana as you can.   I could go on.  Specialization is nice but its the ability to wear different hats, that of a warrior and a cleric, depending upon the situation or both hats when need be that makes the class incredibly fun to play.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ualwayyzforeverr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alwayyz Foreverr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/wizard/chriscain/Alwayyz_mb_sig.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(3/12/02 10:17:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><im